Overview

Lavonia Campground is a scenic Texas getaway just beyond the Dallas metropolitan area. Here, visitors can swim, hike or boat the day away on the waters of Lavon Lake and surrounding area.

Natural Features:

The Lavon Lake, in northern Texas, spans 21,400 acres and stems from the East Fork of the Trinity River.

Recreation:

Visitors of all ages can enjoy activities like fishing, boating and picnicking. Anglers seek species like channel catfish, crappie and striped bass.

Facilities:

The campground offers 53 sites with water and electric hookups. Additional perks include hot showers,swimming and a boat launch.

Nearby Attractions:

The paved Sister Groves Trail at Sister Grove Creek is a hot spot for biking and hiking.
properties.FacilityDirections: From Wylie, take Highway 78 east to County Route 486 (Lake Road).Follow signs into the campground.
